    "safety_guide_wqFCz8": {
      "type": "safety-guide",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_ttzUb8": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "left_header": "<p>How To Use</p>",
            "right_header": "<p>Safety Guidelines</p>"
          }
        },
        "left_text_wrPCPY": {
          "type": "left_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Fill the device:</strong> Open the device and pour in one ampoule of serum.</p>"
          }
        },
        "left_text_HeyLTm": {
          "type": "left_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Prepare the device:</strong> Twist on the needle head and leave upside down for 1–2 minutes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "left_text_adHtgX": {
          "type": "left_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Begin infusion:</strong> Stamp evenly across the face with 2–3 passes, then pat in any remaining serum.</p>"
          }
        },
        "left_tip_TJREht": {
          "type": "left_tip",
          "settings": {
            "tip": "<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Apply remaining serum after your treatment and allow it to absorb overnight.</p>"
          }
        },
        "right_text_WdEqVa": {
          "type": "right_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Micro-Infusion is a simple treatment you can do at-home. No appointments and no downtime. It’s designed to be safe and easy to use, as long as your skin is clean and healthy. </p>"
          }
        },
        "right_text_X4DfHq": {
          "type": "right_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Avoid using Micro-Infusion on active breakouts or broken skin, as it may spread bacteria. Always use a fresh, sterile needle head for each treatment, and apply SPF after use to protect your skin.</p>"
          }
        },
        "right_text_39VN4z": {
          "type": "right_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If you’re pregnant or have a medical condition, check with your doctor first.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_ttzUb8",
        "left_text_wrPCPY",
        "left_text_HeyLTm",
        "left_text_adHtgX",
        "left_tip_TJREht",
        "right_text_WdEqVa",
        "right_text_X4DfHq",
        "right_text_39VN4z"
      ],
      "name": "t:sections.safety-guide.name",
      "settings": {
        "heading": "What you should know for the best results",
        "text": "<p>The Qure Micro-Infusion System is designed with your safety in mind.</p><p>Unlike popular at-home derma rollers, our stamper device features single-use sterile heads that help minimize the risk of infection or unnecessary skin damage caused by blunt and multi-use needles.</p><p>Below are a few rules you should follow while using your Qure Micro-Infusion System:</p>",
        "button_label": "See Detailed Treatment Guide",
        "button_url": "https://qureskincare.com/pages/microinfusion-safety-guide"
      }
    },
    "faq_fkEgqb": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_mmVCEW": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What are the benefits of Micro-Infusion?",
            "text": "<p>The needles of the Micro-Infusion device and the stamping action triggers the body’s natural healing process and in turn boosts the production of collage, making your look firmer and fine lines look softer.</p><p>The serum that you choose to infuse during your Micro-Infusion will determine the major benefits of your treatment. Very fine needles infuse micro-droplets of concentrated serum at a specific depth into the dermis (top layer) of your skin precisely where they are needed to accelerate absorption of active ingredients that target specific skin concerns.</p><p>You can switch up your treatments and even mix the two serums together!</p><p><em>Visible benefits of Micro-Infusion include:</em></p><ul><li>More even skin tone and texture</li><li>Glowing, fresh complexion</li><li>Softer fine lines</li><li>Firmer, rejuvenated skin</li></ul>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_htiCtP": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How quickly will I see results?",
            "text": "<p>Micro-Infusion treatment is an effective skin booster treatment, and you’ll notice a radiance boost, smaller pores, more hydrated and overall a healthy fresh complexion in the next day or two.</p><p>The more treatments you perform the greater skin benefits over time you’ll receive! This quick and easy home facial is perfect to perform a day or two before a big event, when you need to look to boost your skin’s complexion, fast.</p><p>Don’t forget to keep up with your everyday skincare routine to boost the effectiveness of your Micro-Infusion results and keep skin glowing long-term.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_NHQ8bW": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is it painful to use?",
            "text": "<p>You get to experience minimal discomfort and maximum results with Qure's Micro-Infusion System.</p><p>Although the needles themselves are actually longer than most at-home needling systems (making it more effective), the ultra-fine needles are thinner than a human hair, so that means you’ll feel minimal to no pain during treatment.</p><p>During the initial stages of treatment, you may experience a slight sensation or prickling feeling as the needles make contact with the skin but you’ll quickly get used to the feeling quickly.\\</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_YEAApx": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How often can I use the treatment?",
            "text": "<p>We recommend a Micro-Infusion treatment once every 2 weeks for the best results.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_neQaze": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "When is the best time to do Micro-Infusion?",
            "text": "<p>We recommend doing the treatment at night before bed. Avoid being in the sun and using makeup for 24 hours after the treatment. For more information on post treatment care, [link][/link].</p>",
            "link_url": "https://qureskincare.com/pages/microinfusion-safety-guide?ref=49949480-3b91-401e-9cd9-888a90834e70",
            "link_text": "visit our safety guide"
          }
        },
        "accordion_hi3Tff": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I use it around the eyes and on the neck?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, you can use Micro-Infusion around the eye area to help smooth crow’s feet. Just ensure to apply a very gentle pressure and only do one pass. Monitor your skin accordingly as everyone’s skin is different!</p><p>Performing Micro-Infusion on the neck can help improve the appearance of fine lines, and rejuvenate skin. It can target issues such as neck creases, horizontal lines, and age-related skin concerns to help enhance the overall texture, tone, and youthfulness of the skin.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_xadEkb": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I use a different serum with the Micro-Infusion device?",
            "text": "<p>No - only use the provided Qure serum with your Micro-Infusion Device.</p><p>Please keep in mind that not all serums are suitable for Micro-Infusion. Some may cause irritation and should be avoided! Our potent serum ampoules are specifically developed for our Micro-Infusion System, with gentle, fragrance-free formulas designed for deep elivery and low risk of sensitivity.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_LpkpA7": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How is this different to micro-rolling?",
            "text": "<p>Micro-needling focuses on stimulating your body's own collagen by creating micro-injuries. But it doesn’t deliver any ingredients directly into your skin.</p><p>With Micro-Infusion, you not only reap the benefits of micro-needling, but also deliver active ingredient solutions to target your specific skin concerns - This makes it work quicker and more effectively.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_4ber4J": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Tranexamic Acid Notice",
            "text": "<p>If you live in Australia, you may receive a notice from Border Force regarding tranexamic acid (TXA) in your order. Here’s what you need to know:</p><p>In Australia, TXA is classified as a Schedule 4 (prescription-only) drug only when usedorally or by injection for treating melasma or other medical conditions. However, <strong>topical TXA in cosmetic formulations is permitted.</strong></p><p>Our serums are purely for cosmetic use and do not claim to treat medical conditions. They are applied topically (not injected) and are classified as a cosmetic product rather than a prescription medicine.</p><p>Our products are compliant with Australian regulartions. Facial serums containing up to 3% TXA for cosmetic purposes are not classified as prescription-only medicines and do not require inclusion in the Australian Register of Therapeutic Goods (ARTG).</p><p>If Border Force requires clarification, you can provide the information above to confirm that the product complies with Australian regulations. If further details are needed, they can refer to the Therapeutic Goods Administration (TGA) guidelines on cosmetic formulations.</p><p>If you need further assistance, feel free to [link][/link] —we’re happy to help!</p>",
            "link_url": "#",
            "link_text": "contact our support team"
          }
        }
      },
